{"author":{"id":"d090680751e9d81548e628ee372337dbb14df0993593a8afe125eaa85e30d5d8"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1686034248,"nonce":"vPYfbuRb9erpumrP/50cvBPB3OE=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s5n5yar","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5344","origin":"github"},"title":"GTDB-Tk output files missing","message":"I am reviewing a ticket from a user who is missing output files from their GTDB-Tk jobs.\nOn closer inspection it seems that the wrapper might not be picking up some of the output files, due to an error in the `discover_datasets` declaration. To debug this, I have run `gtdb classify_wf` manually on the CLI and observed the outputs produced by the same run. The user reported that the `.tree` and `.fasta` outputs were missing, but I can see them in the output directory of my local run. It seems that the `output_dir` of `discover_datasets` is incorrect, leading to silent failure and empty collection outputs with `success` status.\n\nOutputs declared in the wrapper:\n\nhttps://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/f173f58bc695c22364685c2ffbb9f3e95708f00f/tools/gtdbtk/gtdbtk_classify_wf.xml#L52-L65\n\n`output_dir` as seen on the server: \n\n```\n.\nв”њв”Ђв”Ђ align\nв”‚В В  в”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.bac120.filtered.tsv\nв”‚В В  в”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.bac120.msa.fasta.gz\nв”‚В В  в””в”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.bac120.user_msa.fasta.gz\nв”њв”Ђв”Ђ classify\nв”‚В В  в”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.bac120.classify.tree.1.tree\nв”‚В В  в”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.bac120.classify.tree.3.tree\nв”‚В В  в”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.bac120.classify.tree.4.tree\nв”‚В В  в”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.bac120.classify.tree.6.tree\nв”‚В В  в”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.bac120.classify.tree.7.tree\nв”‚В В  в”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.bac120.summary.tsv\nв”‚В В  в”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.bac120.tree.mapping.tsv\nв”‚В В  в””в”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.backbone.bac120.classify.tree\nв”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.bac120.summary.tsv -\u003e classify/gtdbtk.bac120.summary.tsv\nв”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.json\nв”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.log\nв”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.warnings.log\nв””в”Ђв”Ђ identify\n    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.ar53.markers_summary.tsv\n    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.bac120.markers_summary.tsv\n    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.failed_genomes.tsv\n    в””в”Ђв”Ђ gtdbtk.translation_table_summary.tsv\n```\n\nSo it seems that the directory for `output_newick` and `output_fasta` are incorrect:\n\n```xml\n\u003c!-- dir should be \"output_dir/classify\" --\u003e\n\u003cdiscover_datasets pattern=\"(?P\u0026lt;designation\u0026gt;.+)\\.tree\" ext=\"newick\" directory=\"output_dir\"/\u003e\n\n\u003c!-- dir should be \"output_dir/align\" --\u003e\n\u003cdiscover_datasets pattern=\"(?P\u0026lt;designation\u0026gt;.+)\\.fasta\" ext=\"fasta\" directory=\"output_dir\"/\u003e\n```","files":null}]}